Subject: Re: [T2] Push rod tube seals on an upright engine

On 3/2/06 4:20 PM, "John Baker" <harmony(-at-)buszen.com> wrote:

> To replace push rod tube seals on a T1 engine (1600 DP
> Bus engine), heads must be removed, is this correct???

You can get some expanding PR tubes. Then what you do is remove the rockers
and pushrods, destroy the old PR tubes to get them out, and install the
expanding type tubes.


